defs.name: SegQueue
defs.docs:
A Michael-Scott queue that allocates "segments" (arrays of nodes)

defs.name: chase_lev
defs.docs: A lock-free concurrent work-stealing deque

defs.name: Worker
defs.docs:
Worker half of the work-stealing deque. This worker has exclusive access to
 one side of the deque, and uses `push` and `try_pop` method to manipulate it.

defs.name: Stealer
defs.docs:
The stealing half of the work-stealing deque. Stealers have access to the
 opposite end of the deque from the worker, and they only have access to the
 `steal` method.

defs.name: Empty
defs.docs: The deque was empty at the time of stealing

defs.name: Abort
defs.docs:
The stealer lost the race for stealing data, and a retry may return more
 data.

defs.name: Data
defs.docs: The stealer has successfully stolen some data.

defs.name: Steal
defs.docs: When stealing some data, this is an enumeration of the possible outcomes.

defs.name: deque
defs.docs: Creates a new empty deque

defs.name: ArcCell
